NodeJS.

    - NodeJS is the Server Side Scripting language.
    - By using NodeJS we can create http & tcp servers.
    - in general we will prepare Node Applications by using javascript.
    - node will support the modules to build server.

modules in nodejs
-----------------
1. http
    - by using this module we can create http server.

2. mysql
    - by using this module we can interact with the mysql database

3. mongodb
    - by using this module we can interact with the mongodb.

4. fs
    - "fs" stands for file system.
    - by using this module we can interact with the flat files(text files), xml files , json files.....

5. express
    - by using this module we can develop the REST API.

6. body-parser
    - by using this module we can set the MIME Type.

    Ex.

        json
        xml
        text
        --
        --
        --
7. multer
    - this module used to handle the file uploadings to server.


 - in general we will download required modules by using "package.json" file.

 - we can install the modules by using "npm install" command

 - we can start the server by using "npm start" commnad.


Example_1:
     Launch Angular application by using node server.


----------------------
Basic_NodeEx
    index.html
    package.json
    server.js
----------------------


package.json
-
{
    "name":"nareshit",
    "version":"1.0.0",
    "description":"First Node Example !",
    "dependencies":{
        "express":"latest"
    }
}

>npm install

server.js
-
//import express module
var express = require("express");

//create the server
var app = express();

//Deploy the application
app.use(express.static(__dirname+"/../Basic_NodeEx"));

//Assign the Port No.
app.listen(8080);
console.log("Server Listening the Port No.8080");


>npm start


open the browser:

http://localhost:8080



Example_2:
    interact with the "mysql database"

---------------
Node_MySQLEx
    index.html
    package.json
    server.js
---------------

create the schema (database)
>create schema demo_classes;

switch the database
>use demo_classes;

create the table
>create table emp(eno integer,ename varchar(20),eage integer)

insert the data
>insert into emp values(111,'emp_1',20);


fetch the data
-
>select * from emp;




server.js
-

var express = require("express");
var mysql = require("mysql");

//connection object.
var connection = mysql.createConnection({
    host:"localhost",
    user : "root",
    password:"root",
    database : "demo_classes"
});


//connect to database.
connection.connect();


//create the get request
app.get("/emp" , function(req,res){
   connection.query("select * from emp", function(err,records,fields){
        res.send(records);
   });
});


mongodb:
-
    - mongodb is the ligth weigth database compared to other databases.

    - mongodb supports JSON.

    - we can perform the CRUD Operations on JSON by using MongoDB.

Installation Of MongoDB:
------------------------
website : https://www.mongodb.com/download-center?jmp=nav#community

    - mongodb follows the client server architecture.

mongodb operations:
-
start the server
>mongod

connect to server(mongo server)
>mongo

    - in genaral mongo server running on the port no : 27017
                                                     : mongodb (protocol)


show the databases:
>show dbs;

create and switch to database:
>use demo;
    [Note : automatically demo database will create and switches to database]


create the collection
>db.createCollection("emp");

insert the data
>db.emp.insert({'id':1,'name':'Hello_1','age':20});


fetch the data
>db.emp.find()









































